    "body": "@akshayku for Go, there is no \"official\" OpenSSL library, so we most likely will not provide first-party support for it.  However, I did find a wrapper [here](https://github.com/spacemonkeygo/openssl) that could be used.\r\n\r\nIn gRPC-Go, support in our library for OpenSSL (or any other transport security) is not required for you to be able to use it. Transport security is very flexible - you would need to create a type that implements [credentials.TransportCredentials](https://godoc.org/google.golang.org/grpc/credentials#TransportCredentials) and pass that to your clients and servers using [grpc.WithTransportCreds](https://godoc.org/google.golang.org/grpc#WithTransportCredentials) and [grpc.Creds](https://godoc.org/google.golang.org/grpc#Creds).  The client and server handshakers are passed the raw network connection and give back a `net.Conn` whose `Read` and `Write` methods are overridden to decrypt/encrypt as appropriate around those operations on the underlying connection.  Please let us know if you have any questions or concerns or if you run into any problems with implementation."
  },
