    "body": "> Which language projections of gRPC uses OpenSSL?\r\n\r\nI think only Go and possibly some wrapped languages do not use OpenSSL.\r\n\r\n> What do you mean by no \"official\" OpenSSL library? If there is none, which one gRPC uses?\r\n\r\ngRPC-Go does not have any integration with OpenSSL.  However, it should be possible to use \r\nOpenSSL with gRPC-Go by implementing `credentials.TransportCredentials`.  I believe the fastest way to get this working would be to use an existing OpenSSL CGo wrapper library like the one linked above.\r\n\r\n> What issues do you see supporting ENGINE (only for places where you call openSSL)?\r\n\r\nI'll leave this for the C/C++ & Java experts to answer.\r\n\r\n> How is your \"credentials.TransportCredentials\" reference different from \"MetadataCredentialsPlugin\" class? Are there any examples of \"TransportCredentials\" that I can fork in the source code?\r\n\r\nSorry, I am not familiar with `MetadataCredentialsPlugin` to compare them.  We have an implementation of `TransportCredentials` in the grpc-go repo for TLS that you could use as a reference:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/grpc/grpc-go/blob/495133b619416f2b99dacb9b23d4da53a0f54d10/credentials/credentials.go#L155:6\r\n"
  },
